Subject: [PATCH 03/11] fix(net): validate Domain= cookie scope and restrict
 jar permissions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

COOK-01: reject a Set-Cookie / document.cookie whose explicit Domain= the request host is not under, or that is a public suffix — blocking cross-site cookie injection / session fixation (host-relationship + best-effort public-suffix list, no new dependency). COOK-06: persist cookies.json with 0o600 permissions on unix.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

